        public static final int TIMEOUT_ACTION_NOTIFICATION
        Constant to notify the listener on timeout.

        When the timeout action is notification, the timeout resets on each notification and the listener is again on the next timeout. This repeats until the listener is explicitly removed.

      • getLowerBoundPercent

        public int getLowerBoundPercent()
        CPU availability lower bound percent.

        CPU availability change notifications are sent when the CPU availability reaches or decreases below this value. The value of this field must be less than the value of mUpperBoundPercent.

        To avoid spurious or very frequent notifications, the delta between the upper bound percent and lower bound percent must be reasonably large.

        To ignore this field, specify IGNORE_PERCENT_LOWER_BOUND as the value. Must not ignore both this field and mUpperBoundPercent in the same configuration.

      • getUpperBoundPercent

        public int getUpperBoundPercent()
        CPU availability upper bound percent.

        CPU availability change notifications are sent when the CPU availability reaches or increases above this value. The value of this field must be greater than the value of mLowerBoundPercent.

        To avoid spurious or very frequent notifications, the delta between the upper bound percent and lower bound percent must be reasonably large.

        To ignore this field, specify IGNORE_PERCENT_UPPER_BOUND as the value. Must not ignore both this field and mLowerBoundPercent in the same configuration.

      • getTimeoutInSeconds

        public long getTimeoutInSeconds()
        CPU availability monitoring timeout in seconds.

        To avoid timing out, specify MONITORING_TIMEOUT_NEVER as the value.

      • getTimeoutAction

        public int getTimeoutAction()
        Action to take on timeout. Specify one of the TIMEOUT_ACTION_* constants.

        When the value of mTimeoutInSeconds is MONITORING_TIMEOUT_NEVER, this field is ignored.
